The treat here is 15. 0-0 Bxf3 16. Rxf3 Qxc4 winning a pawn. So I had to defend or move my bishop. I didn't played Qd3 cause I thought that there would be many pins after some rook goes to d8. So I decided to move the bishop and I needed it to be behind my queen so that I can manage a mate attack or something in the future. Thats why I played it on a2.
